tags: no one should be reading scans of the shonen jump series at this point
summary: Reading the early weekly shonen jump scans then reading the official translations is NOT supporting the official...
body:
Reading the early weekly shonen jump scans then reading the official translations is NOT supporting the official release.

Reading the illegal scans while claiming it’s okay bc you buy merch/volumes is NOT supporting the release.

Reading and posting images of the chapters before the official translations are out is NOT supporting the official release.

Choosing to still read the scans instead of the free, totally legal, globally available simulpub chapters is NOT SUPPORTING THE OFFICIAL RELEASE.

‘Early’ doesn’t cut it (guess what? You still have to wait ~7 days in between chapters, so why can’t you switch the day you read the chapters????)

'I don’t like the official translations’ is also a lousy, twisted excuse not to support the official release.

Reading the leaked weekly shonen jump scans in any shape or form at this point is unacceptable; you are encouraging the continuation of this activity no matter how you cut it. There’s no excuse anymore. No one should be reading jump scans.

body:
Overhaul bf headcanons

  • In all honesty, Chisaki Kai isn’t what you’d call a romantic, even if he is sentimental to some degree, or is at least capable of caring for someone. Case in point, the former leader of his gang: part of the reason Overhaul, or Chisaki, took the actions he did were to repay someone he felt a sense of responsibility to for the kindness they showed him. So yes, Chisaki can feel emotion for others: loyalty, respect, even admiration.
  • That being said, these emotions are limited and aren’t always expressed in what you could call positive ways. Whether it’s intentional or just a naturally warped mindset, Chisaki will always put himself first.
  • The things you desire and need will be incorporated into an established outline of what Chisaki has deemed as important or worth his time and effort. For whatever reason, he has found himself attached to you.
  • Chisaki will rarely touch you for the sake of it. Not that he finds you diseased or disgusting. He just can’t bring himself to do it, but even if he could, Chisaki isn’t one to express emotions in a conventional way.
  • He won’t spend on you frivulously, unless what you have your eye on also happens to be expensive. Help with rent or your own apartment, clothes, jewelry, meals, toys, sweets, whatever material things you like, Chisaki will get as long as it’s in the realm of affordable.
  • Chisaki for all his selfishness and cold outlook on most things, will not intend to hurt or harm you. He honestly believes that the outcome outweighs the means. He is right and he knows what is best for you and what will ultimately benefit you the most.
  • As long as Chisaki doesn’t have to put aside his own goals and desires, he might even make you strangely happy. He won’t look at others, he won’t needlessly bad mouth you, start arguments, strike you, or treat you disrespectfully like one might expect a gang member to. In his own fashion, he will look out for you, but as stated, everything is on his terms.
  • Chisaki won’t take no for an answer. It doesn’t matter if you didn’t actually agree to be with him or have rejected him. He still considers you his because it’s what he wants. You’re just being stubborn or ignorant of what you’re missing out on.
  • So in a way, Chisaki respects you but to an extent; he couldn’t care for someone he doesn’t respect at all. Chisaki also wants to see you content and safe, but it has to be with him, through him. He is controlling, and worse yet, you might not even recognize it.
  • You’ll be calmly sweet talked, rationalized with, persuaded, but with a determined and almost forceful edge to every proposal and suggestion. It’s only after complete and utter disobedience will Chisaki lose patience and just plow on to outright force.
  • He still wants you to like him though. In a way, any perceived rejection will be met with bitterness and irritation. Chisaki doesn’t know how to be sad; sadness equates to hopelessness and hopelessness equals defeat. Anger motivates and leads to action, though it also neglects deliberate and careful thought. Not that Chisaki is all that empathetic in a pleased state.
  • Possessive is an understatement. Chisaki considers your conduct toward him as a reflection of your view of him. You will be faithful and keep the the boundaries he sets.
  • Do not test him. Chisaki will take offense. Don’t lie. Don’t question him, or if you do, you better be tactful and the definition of respectful.
  • It’s bad enough he’s become attached; Chisaki would just ignore his feelings, but if he can find a way to have it all, he will. And he does want you.
  • Think that quote from Labyrinth; it applies to Chisaki more than he even cares to admit.
  • “Just fear me, love me, do as I say and I will be your slave.”
  • If you do what’s expected, if you obey, and what’s more, if you genuinely do express your gratitude and affection, Chisaki will almost be gentle. In his best mood, he will perform little gestures of physical affection-a hand on your shoulder, lingering as you pass him objects, the tips of ungloved fingers ghosting over your cheek or arm, a chaste kiss to your forehead. He will even take the time to listen to you, (even if what you speak of seems trivial to him) take you places you want to go, (even if he might refuse to take part in certain activities) as long as it fits his schedule.
  • The sex had is intense, whether it be slow, hard, fast, gentle, etc. The pleasure derived is good, but the meaning of the act is everything. Chisaki’s mood will affect the pace and tone of each encounter, but you will always be left dizzy and weak kneed.
  • He will kill for you, no questions asked, no hesitation. He will shut down anyone speaking badly of you, will snap at any hint of mistreatment. Even if he himself is guilty of emotional manipulation and the like, in Chisaki’s eyes, it simply is not the same.
  • It’s a self serving kind of love, but it’s all Chisaki is willing to give. It might be all he can give at this point. But it is love and it’s sincere, even if it is twisted.

  • Do not test him. Chisaki will take offense. Don’t lie. Don’t question him, or if you do, you better be tactful and the definition of respectful.
  • It’s bad enough he’s become attached; Chisaki would just ignore his feelings, but if he can find a way to have it all, he will. And he does want you.
  • Think that quote from Labyrinth; it applies to Chisaki more than he even cares to admit.
  • “Just fear me, love me, do as I say and I will be your slave.”
  • If you do what’s expected, if you obey, and what’s more, if you genuinely do express your gratitude and affection, Chisaki will almost be gentle. In his best mood, he will perform little gestures of physical affection-a hand on your shoulder, lingering as you pass him objects, the tips of ungloved fingers ghosting over your cheek or arm, a chaste kiss to your forehead. He will even take the time to listen to you, (even if what you speak of seems trivial to him) take you places you want to go, (even if he might refuse to take part in certain activities) as long as it fits his schedule.
  • The sex had is intense, whether it be slow, hard, fast, gentle, etc. The pleasure derived is good, but the meaning of the act is everything. Chisaki’s mood will affect the pace and tone of each encounter, but you will always be left dizzy and weak kneed.

  • It’s a self serving kind of love, but it’s all Chisaki is willing to give. It might be all he can give at this point. But it is love and it’s sincere, even if it is twisted.

Overhaul bf headcanons

  • In all honesty, Chisaki Kai isn’t what you’d call a romantic, even if he is sentimental to some degree, or is at least capable of caring for someone. Case in point, the former leader of his gang: part of the reason Overhaul, or Chisaki, took the actions he did were to repay someone he felt a sense of responsibility to for the kindness they showed him. So yes, Chisaki can feel emotion for others: loyalty, respect, even admiration.
  • That being said, these emotions are limited and aren’t always expressed in what you could call positive ways. Whether it’s intentional or just a naturally warped mindset, Chisaki will always put himself first.
  • The things you desire and need will be incorporated into an established outline of what Chisaki has deemed as important or worth his time and effort. For whatever reason, he has found himself attached to you.
  • Chisaki will rarely touch you for the sake of it. Not that he finds you diseased or disgusting. He just can’t bring himself to do it, but even if he could, Chisaki isn’t one to express emotions in a conventional way.
  • He won’t spend on you frivulously, unless what you have your eye on also happens to be expensive. Help with rent or your own apartment, clothes, jewelry, meals, toys, sweets, whatever material things you like, Chisaki will get as long as it’s in the realm of affordable.
  • Chisaki for all his selfishness and cold outlook on most things, will not intend to hurt or harm you. He honestly believes that the outcome outweighs the means. He is right and he knows what is best for you and what will ultimately benefit you the most.
  • As long as Chisaki doesn’t have to put aside his own goals and desires, he might even make you strangely happy. He won’t look at others, he won’t needlessly bad mouth you, start arguments, strike you, or treat you disrespectfully like one might expect a gang member to. In his own fashion, he will look out for you, but as stated, everything is on his terms.
  • Chisaki won’t take no for an answer. It doesn’t matter if you didn’t actually agree to be with him or have rejected him. He still considers you his because it’s what he wants. You’re just being stubborn or ignorant of what you’re missing out on.
  • So in a way, Chisaki respects you but to an extent; he couldn’t care for someone he doesn’t respect at all. Chisaki also wants to see you content and safe, but it has to be with him, through him. He is controlling, and worse yet, you might not even recognize it.
  • You’ll be calmly sweet talked, rationalized with, persuaded, but with a determined and almost forceful edge to every proposal and suggestion. It’s only after complete and utter disobedience will Chisaki lose patience and just plow on to outright force.
  • He still wants you to like him though. In a way, any perceived rejection will be met with bitterness and irritation. Chisaki doesn’t know how to be sad; sadness equates to hopelessness and hopelessness equals defeat. Anger motivates and leads to action, though it also neglects deliberate and careful thought.
